237 batch_per_txn_);
238 if (!status.ok()) {
239 break;
240 }
241 SequenceNumber seq_of_batch = WriteBatchInternal::Sequence(&batch);
242 std::vector<uint32_t> column_family_ids;
243 status = CollectColumnFamilyIdsFromWriteBatch(batch, &column_family_ids);
244 if (status.ok()) {
245 for (const auto id : column_family_ids) {
246 ColumnFamilyData* cfd =
247 versions_->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetColumnFamily(id);
248 if (cfd == nullptr) {
249 continue;
250 }
251 cfds_changed->insert(cfd);
252 const std::vector<FileMetaData*>& l0_files =
253 cfd->current()->storage_info()->LevelFiles(0);
254 SequenceNumber seq =
255 l0_files.empty() ? 0 : l0_files.back()->fd.largest_seqno;
256 // If the write batch's sequence number is smaller than the last
257 // sequence number of the largest sequence persisted for this column
258 // family, then its data must reside in an SST that has already been
259 // added in the prior MANIFEST replay.
260 if (seq_of_batch <= seq) {
261 continue;
262 }
263 auto curr_log_num = std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max();
264 if (cfd_to_current_log_.count(cfd) > 0) {
265 curr_log_num = cfd_to_current_log_[cfd];
266 }
267 // If the active memtable contains records added by replaying an
268 // earlier WAL, then we need to seal the memtable, add it to the
269 // immutable memtable list and create a new active memtable.
270 if (!cfd->mem()->IsEmpty() &&
271 (curr_log_num == std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max() ||
272 curr_log_num != log_number)) {
273 const MutableCFOptions mutable_cf_options =
274 *cfd->GetLatestMutableCFOptions();
275 MemTable* new_mem =
276 cfd->ConstructNewMemtable(mutable_cf_options, seq_of_batch);
277 cfd->mem()->SetNextLogNumber(log_number);
278 cfd->mem()->ConstructFragmentedRangeTombstones();
279 cfd->imm()->Add(cfd->mem(), &job_context->memtables_to_free);
280 new_mem->Ref();
281 cfd->SetMemtable(new_mem);
282 }
283 }
284 bool has_valid_writes = false;
285 status = WriteBatchInternal::InsertInto(
286 &batch, column_family_memtables_.get(),
287 nullptr /* flush_scheduler */, nullptr /* trim_history_scheduler*/,
288 true, log_number, this, false /* concurrent_memtable_writes */,
289 next_sequence, &has_valid_writes, seq_per_batch_, batch_per_txn_);
290 }
291 // If column family was not found, it might mean that the WAL write
292 // batch references to the column family that was dropped after the
293 // insert. We don't want to fail the whole write batch in that case --
294 // we just ignore the update.
295 // That's why we set ignore missing column families to true
296 // passing null flush_scheduler will disable memtable flushing which is
297 // needed for secondary instances
298 if (status.ok()) {
299 for (const auto id : column_family_ids) {
300 ColumnFamilyData* cfd =
301 versions_->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetColumnFamily(id);
302 if (cfd == nullptr) {
303 continue;
304 }
305 std::unordered_map<ColumnFamilyData*, uint64_t>::iterator iter =
306 cfd_to_current_log_.find(cfd);
307 if (iter == cfd_to_current_log_.end()) {
308 cfd_to_current_log_.insert({cfd, log_number});
309 } else if (log_number > iter->second) {
310 iter->second = log_number;
311 }
312 }
313 auto last_sequence = *next_sequence - 1;
314 if ((*next_sequence != kMaxSequenceNumber) &&
315 (versions_->LastSequence() <= last_sequence)) {
316 versions_->SetLastAllocatedSequence(last_sequence);
317 versions_->SetLastPublishedSequence(last_sequence);
318 versions_->SetLastSequence(last_sequence);
319 }
320 } else {
321 // We are treating this as a failure while reading since we read valid
322 // blocks that do not form coherent data
323 reader->GetReporter()->Corruption(record.size(), status);
324 }
325 }
326 if (status.ok() && !wal_read_status->ok()) {
327 status = *wal_read_status;
328 }
329 if (!status.ok()) {
330 wal_read_status->PermitUncheckedError();
331 return status;
332 }
333 }
334 // remove logreaders from map after successfully recovering the WAL
335 if (log_readers_.size() > 1) {
336 auto erase_iter = log_readers_.begin();
337 std::advance(erase_iter, log_readers_.size() - 1);
338 log_readers_.erase(log_readers_.begin(), erase_iter);
339 }
340 return status;
341}
